United Soccer Coaches All-North Region Third Team (2021)

AS A SENIOR IN 2023

Earned her second First Team All-Patriot League spot…Named the Patriot League Offensive Player of the Week (Oct. 2)…Named to the Preseason All-Patriot League Team…Appeared in 11 games with 11 starts, totaling 652 minutes…Recorded her first-career brace and scored the game-winning goal and a career-high two goals against Navy (Oct. 1)…Assisted in the first goal of the game with a cross into the box against Bucknell (Oct. 14)...Recorded three points against American (Oct. 21) with one goal and one assist in the team’s 4-0 win…Logged a game-high seven shots against Army West Point (Oct. 25) …Played a season-high 83 minutes against Bucknell (Nov. 2).

AS A JUNIOR IN 2022

2022 Second Team All-Patriot League … 2022 Patriot League All-Tournament Team … 2022 Preseason All-Patriot League Team … Two-time Patriot League Offensive Player of the Week (Aug. 29 and Oct. 10) … One of seven Terriers to start in all 20 games on the season … Ranked second on the team and sixth in the Patriot League with 13 points … Her five assists were tied for fourth in the Patriot League, while her four goals tied for seventh … Scored what proved to be the game-winning goal in the 20th minute at UMass Lowell (Aug. 25) … Followed that up with three points on a goal and an assist against Michigan (Aug. 28) … Assisted on the Terriers’ lone goal against Boston College (Sept. 4) … Added a helper in the win over Navy (Sept. 24) … Buried game’s lone tally in the 16th minute for a road win at No. 25 Harvard (Oct. 4) … Set up the game-winning goal at American (Oct. 8) … Compiled a goal and an assist in the Patriot League quarterfinal round against Loyola Maryland (Oct. 30).

AS A SOPHOMORE IN 2021

All-Patriot League First Team and United Soccer Coaches All-North Region Third Team selection ... Appeared in all 20 games, making 17 starts ... Tied for the team lead with seven assists (T-2nd in the Patriot League) and ranked second with 11 points, adding two goals ... Scored her first collegiate goal against UMass Lowell (Aug. 23) ... Notched her first-career assist on the game-tying goal against Lafayette (Sept. 18) ... Found the back of the net while tallying an assist in the win at Navy (Sept. 25) ... Posted two assists in the victory over Holy Cross (Oct. 13) ... Registered two assists again at Army (Oct. 27) ... Assisted on the game-winning goal in the Patriot League Semifinals against Army (Nov. 4).

AS A FRESHMAN IN 2020-21

Saw action in three games ... Played a season-high 44 minutes at Holy Cross (March 21).

BEFORE BOSTON UNIVERSITY

Three-time all-state, Central Mass All-Star and all-league at Nashoba Regional … Two-time Telegram and Gazette Super Team … Led the league in scoring and guided Nashoba Regional to the state final as a freshman … Played club for FC Stars.

PERSONAL

Parents are Joy and Lawrence McNulty ... Has one brother, Matthew ... Enrolled in Sargent College to major in Health Science at BU.

No stats available for the current season.
